I found this workout had some flaws:
1. Too repetitive. Repeating a circuit twice is less boring. Three times just makes me bored and my muscles fatigue and cramp.
2. Too static. My quads were cramping bc of the lack of mobility with these moves. Plus no stretching between circuits.
3. Rough on knees

Overall glad I did it (with lots of my own modifications) but won't be doing this one again. I prefer the dynamic, fun, and very effective moves of Kit Rich and Marnie Alton.
